# SEO, accessibility, and performance

- Use one clear `h1` per page and a logical heading hierarchy.
- Write semantic HTML before adding custom div-based layouts.
- Every meaningful image needs useful `alt` text. Decorative images should use empty alt text.
- Use descriptive link and button labels. Avoid vague labels such as "click here".
- Keep the landing page fast: avoid heavy libraries, large images, and unnecessary client components.
- Optimize images with correct dimensions, modern formats, and lazy loading where appropriate.
- Preserve keyboard navigation and visible focus states.
- Ensure color contrast is readable on all backgrounds.
- Add page metadata: title, description, Open Graph, favicon, and canonical URL when available.
- Do not add animations that block interaction, harm accessibility, or hurt performance.
